The paper proposes a new method for feature selection using random forests, which is a popular supervised learning algorithm in machine learning. The paper also applies the method to high-dimensional gene data sets, indicating a focus on bioinformatics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). The paper also involves data analysis and statistics, suggesting cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the focus on bioinformatics and gene data sets suggests cs.BIO (Computational Biology) as a less likely but still possible sub-category.
